==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Larkspur
<hw>Lark"spur</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
genus of ranunculaceous plants (<gen>Delphinium</gen>), having showy
flowers, and a spurred calyx. They are natives of the North Temperate
zone. The commonest larkspur of the gardens is <spn>Delphinium
Consolida</spn>. The flower of the bee larkspur (<spn>Delphinium
elatum</spn>) has two petals bearded with yellow hairs, and looks not
unlike a bee.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Larmier</ent>⟦br⟧
